[Credit card numbering scheme]
In article <1992Jan7.155756.3444@doc.ic.ac.uk> dds@doc.ic.ac.uk (Diomidis Spinellis) writes:
> There is an international standard specifying the number codes, and
> their allocation.

For example Mastercard has all numbers beginning with 5, and Visa all
numbers beginning with 4. I believe 1, 2, and 3 each belong to one
organization, with higher numbers being subdivided (i.e. 60 and 61 might
not belong to the same organization).

> The following routine will calculate the checksum number:
[...]
>        return 10 - s % 10;

This should be:

    return (10 - s % 10) % 10;

or

    return (1000 - s) % 10;

Otherwise it returns 10 if the last digit is zero.
